---
description: Use uv for Python project and dependency management
alwaysApply: true
---

When working on Python projects, unless specified otherwise, use uv. This means:
- When working on a new project: `uv init --bare && uv venv -p python3.11`
- Install dependencies using `uv add`
- Source `.venv/bin/activate`
- Don't use `pip install` unless necessary and authorized, and always check that the virtualenv is sourced before installing dependencies.
